Name: Bilal Hadfi
Description: Hadfi had returned from the Middle East to Belgium. Security officials were aware of him but he managed to slip off their radar.

Name: Unknown, previously identifed as Ahmad al-Mohammad
Description: The identity of this suspect is still unknown. Initial reports cited a passport found near the scene of one of the attacks as belonging to Mohammad, tracing his journey into Europe through Greece. However, French authorities later said the passport was a fake.

Name: Omar Ismail Mostefai
Description: Mostefai had a criminal past and was believed to have gone to Syria in 2013. Turkey said it had warned France about Mostefai in the past

Name: Samy Amimour
Description: Amiour grew up in the French city of Drancy and was known to French authorities in 2012. After leaving France for Syria, Amimour's father traveled to Syria to try and convince his son to return home in 2013.

Name: Ibrahim Abdeslam
Description: Abdeslam was the proprietor of a bar in Brussel's Molenbeek district. Abdeslam's ex-wife told reporters he used drugs and was not interested in world affairs

Name: Abdelhamid Abaaoud
Description: He has been described as the mastermind behind the attack. It remains unclear if he is in Europe or Syria. French authorities launched a raid in Saint-Denis Wednesday to try and apprehend him. His own family has said they wished for his death. He had been under surveillance, but authorities at the time said they had no idea he was plotting a major attack

Name: Salah Abdeslam
Description: French authorities said Abdeslam spent time in Austria and he used his credit card to book a hotel room in Alfortville ahead of the attacks. His brother Ibrahim died in the attacks.

Name: Hasna Aitboulahcen (waiting for French authorities confirmation)
